me":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry Thornburgh was born in 1390, in England, his father, Thomas Thornburgh, was 21 and his mother, Jane Dalston, was 36. He married Lady Elizabeth Boothe in 1375, in England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died after 1419."},"et":{"1390–after 1419":"1390–pärast 1419","1390–1419":"1390–1419","1392–Male":"1392–Surnud","1397–Male":"1397–Surnud","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","1395–1498":"1395–1498","1399–Male":"1399–Surnud","1405–1454":"1405–1454","1440–1531":"1440–1531","1370–Male":"1370–Surnud","1355–1399":"1355–1399","1440":"1440","1395":"1395","1370":"1370","1392":"1392","1390":"1390","1389":"1389","1400":"1400","1399":"1399","about 1405":"umbes 1405","1355":"1355","1531":"1531","1454":"1454","1498":"1498","after 1419":"pärast 1419","1397":"1397","1419":"1419","1405":"1405","Selsed, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Selside, Westmorland, England":"Selside, Westmorland, England","England":"England","Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1390–after 1419":"1390–1419 jälkeen","1390–1419":"1390–1419","1392–Male":"1392–Kuollut","1397–Male":"1397–Kuollut","1400–Male":"1400–Kuollut","1395–1498":"1395–1498","1399–Male":"1399–Kuollut","1405–1454":"1405–1454","1440–1531":"1440–1531","1370–Male":"1370–Kuollut","1355–1399":"1355–1399","1440":"1440","1395":"1395","1370":"1370","139